article.headline: Arkansas St. 98, Central Baptist 60
article.story: JONESBORO, Ark. -- Brandon Reed scored 14 points and Trey Finn finished with 13 points and 13 rebounds as Arkansas State defeated Central Baptist 98-60 Tuesday night. Four other players scored in double figures for the Red Wolves (6-5). Jeremy Thomas and Brandon Peterson had 13 apiece while Adam Sterrenberg and Martavius Adams each added 12. Coach John Brady won his 300th career game. Ryan Barnes scored 16 points to lead the Mustangs (9-7). Adams also had seven rebounds in only 12 minutes and scored the first eight points for Arkansas State. Rashad Allison recorded a career-high 11 assists. The Red Wolves never trailed, led by 45 and shot 56.3 percent (36 of 64).
